*   **Data-Hypothesis Alignment**: The "High-Tariff Conversion Rate" (HTCR) is a derived ratio ($HT\_students / Total\_HE\_students$). While mathematically valid, it risks conflating two distinct phenomena: changes in general HE access and changes in selective HE access. If general access increases for a disadvantaged group, the HTCR may artificially deflate even if absolute high-tariff progression remains stable.
